{
  "texts": [
    "This ecology is not static; it is constantly evolving as new differentiations emerge within the primary system and its subsystems.",
    "The primary system can be seen as a complex network of interconnected subsystems, each with its own specific functions and operations.",
    "As these subsystems interact with their environment and each other, they generate new forms of differentiation and complexity.",
    "As the environment of a system is characterized by absolute indeterminacy, the system must continuously adapt and evolve to maintain its relevance and functionality.",
    "Indeterminacy refers to the unpredictable and often chaotic nature of external influences that can impact a system."
  ]
}